<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-exceptions">
  <title>Exceptions: When Things Go Wrong</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
    After studying this chapter, you will:
    </p>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand Java's exception-handling mechanisms.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Be able to use the Java <c>try/catch</c> statement.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know how to design effective exception handlers.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Appreciate the importance of exception handling in program design.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Be able to design your own <c>Exception</c> subclasses.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
